The paper proposes a deep learning approach for missing data imputation in spatio-temporal problems, specifically using a convolution bidirectional-LSTM. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the evaluation on traffic flow data suggest that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of the autoencoder's latent feature representation suggests that the paper may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
